  "texts": [
    "In particular, we can parameterize [33] ΛS αβ (k, q) = ⟨ϕ α (k)| e -iq•r |ϕ β (k + q)⟩ = F S (k, q)e iϕ S (k,q)Cα δ αβ,(93)where α, β are composite indices for the sublattice σ, spin s, and valley τ.",
    "The use of the uppercase Λ denotes that the form factor is expressed in the Chern basis.",
    "The superscript 'S' is short-hand for 'symmetric', and reflects the large U (4) C=1 × U (4) C=-1 symmetry of the density operatorfoot_24 ρ(q) = k d † (k)Λ S (k, q) d(k + q) under independent Chern-number preserving U (4) rotations.",
    "We schematically illustrate these symmetry operations in Fig. 4.In the 'central average' subtraction schemefoot_25 defined in Sec.",
    "2.3.1, the projected Hamiltonian in the chiral-flat limit can be expressed asĤUS = 1 2A q V (q) [δ ρ(q)] † δ ρ(q) (94) δ ρ(q) = ρ(q) -ρ(q), ρ(q) = 1 2 k,G δ G,q tr Λ S (k, G),(95)Remarkably, as we briefly review below, the strong-coupling Hamiltonian ĤUS yields exact Slater determinant ground states in the chiral-flat limit at ν = 0 for any repulsive interaction V (q)."
  ]
